1
00:00:12,117 --> 00:00:14,410
MINISTRY OF EDUCATION

2
00:00:14,494 --> 00:00:15,787
I checked everywhere,

3
00:00:15,870 --> 00:00:17,956
but no CCTV cameras
cover the rooftop at all.

4
00:00:18,039 --> 00:00:21,543
But one from the next-door building
might capture a small part of it.

5
00:00:21,626 --> 00:00:23,628
Can you explain and show me?

6
00:00:23,711 --> 00:00:24,629
Of course.

7
00:00:24,712 --> 00:00:26,339
The quality is terrible though.

8
00:00:26,422 --> 00:00:28,675
-You can barely make anything out.
-Okay.

9
00:00:28,758 --> 00:00:30,176
-Let's see.
-Yes, sir.

10
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:33,680
This is it.

11
00:00:34,180 --> 00:00:36,224
-Can you zoom in?
-Yes.

12
00:00:46,609 --> 00:00:48,153
What if someone was here?

13
00:00:50,071 --> 00:00:52,240
What if someone pushed him off?

14
00:01:18,808 --> 00:01:20,393
What brings you here?

15
00:01:21,060 --> 00:01:22,520
Isn't it chaotic at the ERPB?

16
00:01:22,604 --> 00:01:25,231
It's more chaotic in my mind.

17
00:01:27,233 --> 00:01:29,861
I'm wondering
why you came back to this school,

18
00:01:29,944 --> 00:01:32,071
reported bullying as soon as you arrived,

19
00:01:32,155 --> 00:01:34,782
and are doing this now.

20
00:01:39,287 --> 00:01:40,538
Have you done your homework?

21
00:01:44,709 --> 00:01:45,543
Oh, sorry.

22
00:01:46,127 --> 00:01:47,503
I sounded like a salesperson.

23
00:01:48,296 --> 00:01:50,089
If you know what's going on,

24
00:01:50,590 --> 00:01:51,799
I can tell you everything.

25
00:01:52,842 --> 00:01:55,303
I know you want the ERPB gone.

26
00:01:55,386 --> 00:01:56,638
And why would that be?

27
00:02:02,227 --> 00:02:03,603
Probably because of this.

28
00:02:07,273 --> 00:02:09,817
Heart Pills most recently.
Butterfly Pills two years ago.

29
00:02:10,985 --> 00:02:12,070
What are they now?

30
00:02:12,153 --> 00:02:13,696
Diamond.

31
00:02:15,365 --> 00:02:16,991
I guess you don't have any proof.

32
00:02:17,075 --> 00:02:19,786
Otherwise, you'd have called the police
or arrested me.

33
00:02:19,869 --> 00:02:22,080
But here you are, chatting away with me.

34
00:02:24,707 --> 00:02:27,126
You and Ms. Choi

35
00:02:27,627 --> 00:02:29,671
were made for each other.

36
00:02:30,171 --> 00:02:33,091
You're so alike, sticking your nose
in other people's business.

37
00:02:33,174 --> 00:02:35,677
I wonder if you'll share the same fate.

38
00:02:48,439 --> 00:02:49,440
Hey.

39
00:02:49,941 --> 00:02:52,318
Why are you here?
I said I'm not coming to school.

40
00:02:52,402 --> 00:02:53,486
You punk.

41
00:02:53,569 --> 00:02:56,698
Did you expect me to just say,
"Okay, sure, take care"?

42
00:02:56,781 --> 00:02:58,283
That wouldn't do.

43
00:02:58,366 --> 00:03:00,285
Hey, wait. Come here.

44
00:03:00,952 --> 00:03:03,788
Every time you skip school,
you're injured like this.

45
00:03:03,871 --> 00:03:06,332
Oh, that looks pretty bad.

46
00:03:06,416 --> 00:03:08,251
-Let me put some cream on it.
-I'm fine.

47
00:03:08,334 --> 00:03:09,752
Just stay still.

48
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:13,381
Let's see this side.

49
00:03:14,132 --> 00:03:16,843
I don't know what you've been up to,

50
00:03:16,926 --> 00:03:18,845
but do it at school.

51
00:03:18,928 --> 00:03:20,513
It's the safest place, okay?

52
00:03:21,014 --> 00:03:22,890
The safest place? Since when?

53
00:03:22,974 --> 00:03:24,642
It's not just me.

54
00:03:24,726 --> 00:03:26,978
Lots of teachers
are trying to make it safe.

55
00:03:27,061 --> 00:03:29,647
We'll make school a safe place. I promise.

56
00:03:30,565 --> 00:03:32,108
Here, promise.

57
00:03:34,152 --> 00:03:35,653
That's how you break a finger.

58
00:03:37,780 --> 00:03:38,906
You little punk.

59
00:03:39,490 --> 00:03:41,326
Fine, don't come. I won't either.

60
00:03:41,409 --> 00:03:44,078
I'll follow you around forever.
You think I'm bluffing?

61
00:03:44,162 --> 00:03:46,164
You know what my boyfriend calls me?

62
00:03:46,247 --> 00:03:49,417
Flypaper.
Once I catch you, I never let go.

63
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:52,462
I'm coming to pick you up
tomorrow morning. Got it?

64
00:04:06,225 --> 00:04:08,936
Hey, Gyu-cheol. Good morning.

65
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:11,522
Hey, come on. Breakfast…

66
00:04:11,606 --> 00:04:12,899
Gyu-cheol.

67
00:04:14,609 --> 00:04:16,611
Wait. Oh, come on.

68
00:04:16,694 --> 00:04:17,862
-Cho Gyu-cheol.
-Yes?

69
00:04:17,945 --> 00:04:19,447
I'm his homeroom teacher.

70
00:04:19,530 --> 00:04:21,074
You're students, right?

71
00:04:21,157 --> 00:04:22,492
-Put that out.
-Fucking hell.

72
00:04:23,951 --> 00:04:25,078
Gyu-cheol, come on.

73
00:04:25,161 --> 00:04:26,120
-Let's go.
-See you.

74
00:04:26,204 --> 00:04:27,622
-Don't look.
-We'll call you.

75
00:04:42,804 --> 00:04:44,931
Hey, what the hell are you thinking?

76
00:04:45,431 --> 00:04:48,601
The Samgeori guys who came at you
are now after your ass.

77
00:04:48,684 --> 00:04:50,728
Are you seeing that bitch, Choi Ga-yun?

78
00:04:52,814 --> 00:04:55,358
Do you know what Ms. Choi made me realize?

79
00:04:56,734 --> 00:04:59,445
The school is full of people.

80
00:04:59,529 --> 00:05:01,364
So? What about it?

81
00:05:01,447 --> 00:05:03,991
Imagine they were all customers.

82
00:05:04,075 --> 00:05:05,034
-Get inside.
-Nice.

83
00:05:05,118 --> 00:05:09,330
It'd be easy to dodge the cops
and move the product back and forth.

84
00:05:10,039 --> 00:05:11,624
Best of all,

85
00:05:11,707 --> 00:05:15,086
we'd get hundreds of new customers
every year.

86
00:05:23,094 --> 00:05:24,011
Oh man, it's cold.

87
00:05:24,095 --> 00:05:24,929
Ms. Choi.

88
00:05:29,350 --> 00:05:30,268
Gyu-cheol.

89
00:05:30,351 --> 00:05:31,811
You're in uniform.

90
00:05:32,687 --> 00:05:35,106
I figured I'd come to school properly now.

91
00:05:35,189 --> 00:05:37,024
Hey, that's a great decision.

92
00:05:37,108 --> 00:05:39,235
That's a good boy.

93
00:05:40,820 --> 00:05:43,448
I won't touch your hair
since you have your own style.

94
00:05:43,531 --> 00:05:46,451
You haven't eaten, have you?
Want to grab some <i>gimbap</i>?

95
00:06:15,855 --> 00:06:17,773
I BELIEVE IN YOU, GYU-CHEOL!

96
00:06:34,832 --> 00:06:37,043
If she'd just turned a blind eye
back then,

97
00:06:37,126 --> 00:06:39,587
you two would be married by now.

98
00:06:39,670 --> 00:06:40,505
Right?

99
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:49,931
What's that for?
You're not gonna hit me, are you?

100
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:56,187
You shouldn't do that.

101
00:06:56,771 --> 00:06:59,065
There's already a stir
about excessive punishment.

102
00:06:59,148 --> 00:07:01,484
If you hit me now,

103
00:07:01,567 --> 00:07:03,236
it'd be a real personal vendetta.

104
00:07:06,531 --> 00:07:08,241
So don't make a move.

105
00:07:08,324 --> 00:07:11,536
If you don't do anything,
nothing will happen--

106
00:07:19,835 --> 00:07:21,003
I'm sorry, Inspector.

107
00:07:21,671 --> 00:07:22,797
I was wrong.

108
00:07:23,381 --> 00:07:24,882
I'm really sorry.

109
00:07:24,966 --> 00:07:27,260
I'm really sorry, Inspector.
Please spare me.

110
00:07:27,343 --> 00:07:29,178
I'm sorry.

111
00:07:30,388 --> 00:07:31,472
I was wrong.

112
00:07:31,973 --> 00:07:33,558
Please spare me just this once.

113
00:07:33,641 --> 00:07:35,560
Please. I'm sorry!

114
00:07:35,643 --> 00:07:37,478
TEACH YOU A LESSON

115
00:07:38,437 --> 00:07:39,855
<i>I'm really sorry.</i>

116
00:07:39,939 --> 00:07:42,858
<i>I'm really sorry, Inspector.</i>
<i>Please spare me.</i>

117
00:07:43,484 --> 00:07:45,444
This is exactly
what I was concerned about.

118
00:07:45,528 --> 00:07:46,821
Only a few days ago,

119
00:07:46,904 --> 00:07:49,532
excessive punishment
drove Lee Chi-ho to attempt suicide.

120
00:07:49,615 --> 00:07:52,493
Now, Cho Gyu-cheol, doing well at school,
has been assaulted.

121
00:07:52,577 --> 00:07:54,245
Why do you think this happened?

122
00:07:54,328 --> 00:07:56,080
The ERPB went to Jinwon High,

123
00:07:56,163 --> 00:07:58,583
<i>targeting Cho Gyu-cheol from the start.</i>

124
00:07:59,584 --> 00:08:01,586
<i>They went there for personal revenge,</i>

125
00:08:01,669 --> 00:08:04,589
<i>looking for an excuse to harass him.</i>

126
00:08:05,298 --> 00:08:06,382
<i>In the end,</i>

127
00:08:07,091 --> 00:08:10,011
<i>it was Lee Chi-ho who was sacrificed.</i>

128
00:08:10,761 --> 00:08:12,763
I won't stand by and allow such cruelty.

129
00:08:13,347 --> 00:08:18,352
I will see to it that the ERPB,
fueled by personal revenge, is dismantled.

130
00:08:19,895 --> 00:08:21,856
<i>With opinion polls</i>

131
00:08:21,939 --> 00:08:26,569
<i>showing that more than 50% of the public</i>
<i>support disbanding the ERPB,</i>

132
00:08:26,652 --> 00:08:29,155
<i>the president</i>
<i>is under considerable pressure</i>

133
00:08:29,238 --> 00:08:31,574
<i>during the lame-duck period of his term.</i>

134
00:08:32,074 --> 00:08:35,077
<i>Despite strong resistance</i>
<i>from the opposition party,</i>

135
00:08:35,161 --> 00:08:37,747
<i>the president</i>
<i>has so far kept the ERPB in place.</i>

136
00:08:37,830 --> 00:08:39,749
<i>-But his approval rating is at 20%.</i>
-Hello?

137
00:08:39,832 --> 00:08:42,543
<i>To navigate this</i>
<i>and bring his term to a steady close…</i>

138
00:08:42,627 --> 00:08:44,420
I'll come see you now.

139
00:08:46,672 --> 00:08:48,090
It's the ERPB!

140
00:08:56,557 --> 00:08:58,309
What are you doing here?

141
00:08:58,392 --> 00:09:00,436
The ERPB shouldn't come
to schools anymore.

142
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:04,273
We're neither potential criminals
nor targets of personal revenge.

143
00:09:04,357 --> 00:09:06,484
I'm here to investigate Lee Chi-ho's case.

144
00:09:06,567 --> 00:09:09,278
Why would the ERPB investigate

145
00:09:09,362 --> 00:09:11,822
when they caused
Chi-ho to end up like that?

146
00:09:11,906 --> 00:09:15,326
Do you really think
you can conduct a fair investigation?

147
00:09:26,003 --> 00:09:27,963
<i>The ERPB's duties will be suspended</i>

148
00:09:28,047 --> 00:09:32,176
<i>until the investigation</i>
<i>into the student's suicide attempt</i>

149
00:09:32,259 --> 00:09:34,136
at Jinwon High School

150
00:09:35,054 --> 00:09:36,222
is concluded.

151
00:09:37,723 --> 00:09:38,683
Accordingly,

152
00:09:38,766 --> 00:09:41,227
<i>the duties of the ERPB inspectors</i>

153
00:09:41,936 --> 00:09:42,853
<i>will be suspended.</i>

154
00:09:51,195 --> 00:09:53,698
DEPUTY DIRECTOR BONG GEUN-DAE
ERPB

155
00:10:34,905 --> 00:10:36,157
Hey.

156
00:10:37,032 --> 00:10:39,326
Everything is set.
When do we start selling?

157
00:10:39,410 --> 00:10:41,912
Now that the ERPB's out of the way,
we can get started.

158
00:10:42,747 --> 00:10:45,040
First, send samples
to each school's main dealer.

159
00:10:46,709 --> 00:10:48,461
Have them drum up business with those.

160
00:10:48,544 --> 00:10:51,756
Tell them
once a school hits over 100 customers,

161
00:10:51,839 --> 00:10:54,550
we'll start the drop for real.

162
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:57,386
We'll need a shitload of runners.
Just us isn't enough.

163
00:10:58,804 --> 00:11:01,557
Schools aren't just full of customers.

164
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:03,309
They've got runners too.

165
00:11:03,392 --> 00:11:05,269
And they're all minors.

166
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:07,897
No one suspects students.

167
00:11:08,397 --> 00:11:11,317
And even if they get caught,
they'll get out right away.

168
00:11:11,817 --> 00:11:13,319
Best of all,

169
00:11:13,819 --> 00:11:15,446
they're disposable.

170
00:11:24,455 --> 00:11:27,458
I flip sneakers with this guy
for some pocket money.

171
00:11:28,125 --> 00:11:29,835
But there are so many scams

172
00:11:29,919 --> 00:11:32,755
that people want to check them out
in person.

173
00:11:34,673 --> 00:11:36,759
All you have to do is deliver them.

174
00:11:39,929 --> 00:11:40,763
Okay.

175
00:11:46,769 --> 00:11:47,937
Hey.

176
00:11:48,020 --> 00:11:49,939
Oh, hello.

177
00:11:51,565 --> 00:11:53,943
SOYEON GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

178
00:11:54,026 --> 00:11:55,236
They're the right ones.

179
00:12:02,284 --> 00:12:03,494
Yeah, it checks out.

180
00:12:04,453 --> 00:12:05,287
Here.

181
00:12:05,996 --> 00:12:07,915
How was it? Easy, right?

182
00:12:07,998 --> 00:12:08,916
Wanna do it again?

183
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:10,918
Can I?

184
00:12:11,001 --> 00:12:13,254
If you do, that would be great.

185
00:12:20,177 --> 00:12:22,179
-Hello.
-You're here.

186
00:12:22,263 --> 00:12:23,222
-Gyu-cheol.
-Hey.

187
00:12:23,305 --> 00:12:24,306
You're here.

188
00:12:24,390 --> 00:12:25,891
Go on.

189
00:12:35,109 --> 00:12:36,902
Thanks. Can't wait to wear them.

190
00:12:51,166 --> 00:12:53,419
It's called biodiversity.

191
00:12:53,502 --> 00:12:56,130
There's genetic diversity,
species diversity,

192
00:12:56,213 --> 00:12:57,715
ecosystem diversity…

193
00:12:58,465 --> 00:13:01,135
Jin-hyeok and Ju-won, focus.

194
00:13:01,218 --> 00:13:05,472
Traits within the same species
are determined by genetic information.

195
00:13:05,556 --> 00:13:09,476
So what do we call the part of DNA
that stores this information?

196
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,312
We call it genes.

197
00:13:12,229 --> 00:13:15,274
We're in the middle of class.
What's with everyone today?

198
00:13:15,774 --> 00:13:17,151
Let's all focus.

199
00:13:19,737 --> 00:13:21,030
-Looks good.
-Right?

200
00:13:21,113 --> 00:13:23,324
Hey, is this art class or what?

201
00:13:23,407 --> 00:13:25,367
You're going all out with the brushes.

202
00:13:26,118 --> 00:13:27,703
You don't need this, do you?

203
00:13:27,786 --> 00:13:29,580
You're so pretty with a petite face.

204
00:13:29,663 --> 00:13:30,873
So jealous.

205
00:13:30,956 --> 00:13:33,584
Thanks, but I used to have a big face

206
00:13:34,168 --> 00:13:35,336
like you two.

207
00:13:35,419 --> 00:13:38,380
-Sorry. I actually just lost some weight.
-Really?

208
00:13:39,256 --> 00:13:40,674
What kind of diet was it?

209
00:13:41,425 --> 00:13:42,301
I took pills.

210
00:13:43,928 --> 00:13:45,512
They're hard to get.

211
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:48,057
Try them, and if they work, let me know.

212
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:49,767
-Thanks.
-You sure I can have these?

213
00:13:49,850 --> 00:13:51,518
-Yeah.
-This is crazy.

214
00:13:51,602 --> 00:13:53,103
<i>Pitch done.</i>

215
00:13:53,187 --> 00:13:55,439
<i>I need more samples. Please send them.</i>

216
00:13:56,565 --> 00:13:57,399
Oh, ma'am. I--

217
00:13:57,483 --> 00:13:59,944
Oh, Seong-gu.
Seong-jun was in a motorcycle accident.

218
00:14:00,027 --> 00:14:02,988
I have to go to the hospital,
so tell the class to self-study.

219
00:14:05,282 --> 00:14:09,119
Seong-jun got badly hurt
in a motorcycle accident.

220
00:14:09,203 --> 00:14:11,121
Our teacher's gone to the hospital.

221
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:14,416
Holy shit!

222
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:17,461
Seong-jun's been delivering like crazy
and actually bought a bike.

223
00:14:17,544 --> 00:14:19,463
Fuck, really? Let me see.

224
00:14:20,798 --> 00:14:22,549
-Let me see.
-What is it? Show me too.

225
00:14:22,633 --> 00:14:23,968
-Get lost.
-Hey, wait.

226
00:14:24,051 --> 00:14:26,303
-I'm a fucking genius.
-Why?

227
00:14:26,387 --> 00:14:29,056
We can just take over
that punk Seong-jun's routes. Right?

228
00:14:29,139 --> 00:14:30,224
Right?

229
00:14:32,393 --> 00:14:33,686
-True.
-We're pros.

230
00:14:33,769 --> 00:14:35,980
<i>Doesn't it feel off in school lately?</i>

231
00:14:36,063 --> 00:14:39,692
More kids are absent or leaving early,
and everyone seems kind of distracted.

232
00:14:39,775 --> 00:14:41,527
I'm so scared of kids these days.

233
00:14:41,610 --> 00:14:43,070
When the ERPB was around,

234
00:14:43,153 --> 00:14:46,448
I didn't exactly feel respected,
but I did feel protected.

235
00:14:46,532 --> 00:14:49,034
It feels like we're back
to how things used to be.

236
00:14:57,668 --> 00:14:59,086
LOOKING FOR ADHD MEDS
OK, CAN DO

237
00:15:01,588 --> 00:15:02,506
NEED BEAUTY PILLS

238
00:15:02,589 --> 00:15:04,425
Wow, fucking hell.

239
00:15:05,843 --> 00:15:10,222
We have about 17 schools in Seoul alone,
with roughly 100 orders from each.

240
00:15:10,305 --> 00:15:12,474
Looks like
all that sample-pushing paid off.

241
00:15:17,521 --> 00:15:19,273
Let's start selling for real today.

242
00:15:19,356 --> 00:15:22,026
Then should I blast it out
on Telegram right now?

243
00:15:23,569 --> 00:15:24,945
CHO GYU-CHEOL
DROP IT ONCE PAID

244
00:15:27,573 --> 00:15:28,574
DROP IT ONCE PAID

245
00:15:28,657 --> 00:15:29,742
DROP IT ONCE PAID

246
00:15:46,091 --> 00:15:47,926
Can I go to the nurse's office?

247
00:15:49,136 --> 00:15:51,555
Ma'am, I've got a terrible headache too.

248
00:15:51,638 --> 00:15:55,225
Ma'am, I'm really sorry,
but my stomach hurts so much. Excuse me.

249
00:15:57,561 --> 00:15:58,687
Ma'am.

250
00:15:59,271 --> 00:16:03,776
Well, my grandma is really sick,
so I've got to rush home now.

251
00:16:04,276 --> 00:16:05,527
I'll see you tomorrow.

252
00:16:07,488 --> 00:16:08,489
Damn it.

253
00:16:15,329 --> 00:16:16,538
Hey, I'm coming too.

254
00:16:23,837 --> 00:16:24,963
Hey, Seong-gu.

255
